'''Aims college''', Biratnagar, is a [[Private university|private college]] in [[Biratnagar]], [[Nepal]], which offers [[Bachelor of Business Administration|BBS]], [[Bachelor of Arts|BA]] and [http://cdcsit.edu.np/ BSc.CSIT] programmes. The college has produced some prominent students such as Mr. Sandesh Pokhrel and Ms. Sheela Parajuli who were both toppers in exams held by [[Tribhuvan University|Tribhuwan University]] in BSc.CSIT programmes.
[[Category:Education in Nepal]]

{{primary sources|date=February 2014}} {{Infobox government agency | agency_name = Board of Intermediate and Secondary Education, Abbottabad | type = | nativename = بورڈ برائے متوسط و ثانوی تعلیم، ایبٹ آباد | logo = | logo_width = | logo_caption = | picture = | picture_width = | picture_caption = | formed = {{Start date|1990}} | preceding1 = | preceding2 = <!-- (etc.) --> | dissolved = | superseding = | jurisdiction = {{plainlist| * [[Haripur, Pakistan|Haripur]] * [[Abbottabad]] * [[Mansehra]] * [[Battagram]] * [[Kohistan District, Pakistan|Kohistan]] }} | headquarters = [[Abbottabad]] | coordinates = {{coord|34|9|26.37|N|73|15|7.23|E|display=title}} | motto = | employees = | budget = | minister1_name = | minister1_pfo = | minister2_name = | minister2_pfo = | website = {{URL|biseatd.edu.pk}} }} The '''Board of Intermediate and Secondary Education, Abbottabad''', more commonly known as '''BISE Abbottabad''', is an intermediate and secondary education governmental board located in [[Abbottabad]], [[Khyber Pakhtunkhwa]], [[Pakistan]]. It is authorized with financial and administrative authority to organize, manage, regulate, develop and control intermediate and secondary education in general and accomplish examinations in the institutions affiliated with it. BISE Abbottabad came into being as a result of the break-up of Peshawar Board in 1990 under the North West Frontier Province Board of Intermediate and Secondary Education Act 1990. The organisation building is located on Murree Road, [[Abbottabad]].<ref>{{cite web|title=BISE Abbottabad - profile|url=http://results.urduwire.com/boards/kpk/biseatd/|work=Urdu Wire|accessdate=22 February 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222094648/http://results.urduwire.com/boards/kpk/biseatd/|archivedate=22 February 2014|df=}}</ref>
== Jurisdiction == Jurisdiction includes five districts, namely [[Haripur District|Haripur]], [[Abbottabad]], [[Mansehra]], [[Battagram]] and [[Kohistan District, Pakistan|Kohistan]], encompassing an area of 17,194 square kilometres and a population of 3.47 millions.<ref>{{cite web|title=BISE Abbottabad - Jurisdiction|url=http://biseatd.edu.pk/pages.php?p=19|work=Official website|accessdate=27 January 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140202093140/http://biseatd.edu.pk/pages.php?p=19|archivedate=2 February 2014|df=}}</ref>
