== Reception ==

=== Reviews ===
The game has received generally positive reviews. Notably, Steve Johnson, the founder of a popular gun enthusiast online publication ''The Firearm Blog'', described ''World of Guns'' as "my favorite gun app, without a doubt". Johnson noted his use of the game as a reference guide and learning aid: "I have even used it to figure out how to fit some old mil-surplus guns I own".<ref name="tfb-review" /> [[Rock, Paper, Shotgun]] praised ''World of Guns'' and its earlier iterations on multiple occasions,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2015/11/13/simulation-game-a-to-z/#more-328233|title=''Stone, Tim'' The Flare Path, Alphabetised|website=Rock, Paper, Shotgun|date=November 15, 2015}}</ref><ref name="rps-emilygera">{{cite web|url=https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2015/05/09/world-of-guns-free-ww2-unlocks/|title=''Gera, Emily'' This is my rifle|website=Rock, Paper, Shotgun|date=May 9, 2015}}</ref> at one point comparing it favorably to ''[[Car Mechanic Simulator 2014|Car Mechanic Simulator]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2014/07/15/car-mechanic-simulator-2014-review/|title=''Stone, Tim'' Wot I Think: Car Mechanic Simulator 2014|website=Rock, Paper, Shotgun|date=July 15, 2014}}</ref> RPS reviewers described the game as "disarmingly obsessive and up-front", "mesmerizing", "a pleasing almost ritualistic act",<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2013/03/08/the-flare-path-maxims-to-live-by/#more-144790|title=''Stone, Tim'' The Flare Path: Maxims To Live By|website=Rock, Paper, Shotgun|date=March 8, 2013}}</ref> and noted that "[previously, we] called its gameplay "almost philosophical", which is partly a joke but I think very true".<ref name="rps-emilygera" />

[[TouchArcade]]'s review of the early version of the ''Gun Disassembly'' game was lukewarm (2.5/5 stars), commending it as a "technical app with an extraordinary amount of detail", and "a singular experience", but noting its "limited appeal" and expressing doubts if it qualifies to be called a game.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://toucharcade.com/2010/05/11/gun-disassembly-3d-review-second-amendment-meet-the-app-store/|title=''Lettieri, Peter'' Gun Disassembly 3D Review: Second Amendment, Meet the App Store|website=TouchArcade|date=May 11, 2010}}</ref> Launch Party Gaming reviewer criticized the "pay-to-win" model used by the game, but praised it as a "must have for gun enthusiasts" and a "great simulator" (6.5/10).<ref name="launchparty" /> The review by firearms blog Guns.Com has pointed out that ''World of Guns'' is "a bit rough", but called its core functionality "outstanding" and a "unique resource", described the microtransactions model as "reasonable", and underlined its utility as reference for servicing actual firearms. The reviewer went on to say that "...when I buy a gun I usually check to see if WoG has a model of it, and if there is one, I’ll buy it"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.guns.com/review/gear-review-world-of-guns-software-disassembles-your-guns-virtually/|title=Guns.Com|website=Andy C – Gear Review: World of Guns software disassembles your guns virtually|date=June 6, 2017|accessdate=2017-06-06|language=English}}</ref>. The game was also covered in Russian-language gaming press,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://itc.ua/articles/world-of-guns-gun-disassembly-azbuka-oruzheynika/|title=''Danilov, Oleg'' World of Guns: Gun Disassembly – The Armorer's ABC|website=ITC.ua|date=September 13, 2014|language=Russian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://gamespirit.org/reviews/world-of-guns-gun-disassembly-review/|title=World of Guns: Gun Disassembly Review|website=gamespirit.org|language=Russian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.playground.ru/blogs/world_of_guns_gun_disassembly/world_of_guns_gun_disassembly_virtualnyj_oruzhejnik-100349/|title=World of Guns: Gun Disassembly - Virtual Armorer|website=Playground.ru Blogs|language=Russian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://hi-tech.ua/article/obzor-world-of-guns-gun-disassembly-interaktivnaya-oruzheynaya-entsiklopediya/|title=''Mironovich, Vladislav'' World of Guns: Gun Disassembly Review. Interactive Firearm Encyclopedia|website=high-tech.ua|date=July 29, 2015|language=Russian}}</ref> including a segment on the ''Ot Vinta!'' TV show about videogames.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vk.com/video-295321_171216197|title=The Talos Principle, World of Guns|website=Ot Vinta! with Bonus и Gamover — episode 16|date=February 20, 2015|accessdate=2017-01-15|language=Russian}}</ref>.

=== Popularity ===
According to SteamSpy, 2.2 million Steam users own the game (average rating 82%, "Very Positive").<ref>{{cite web|url=https://steamspy.com/app/262410|title=World of Guns: Gun Disassembly - SteamSpy App Data|accessdate=2017-01-15}}</ref> The ''World of Guns'' app for the [[VK (social networking)|VK.com]] social network has 810,000 installs;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vk.com/gun_disassembly|title=World of Guns: Gun Disassembly on VK.COM|accessdate=2017-01-15}}</ref> the Facebook app lists 10,000 monthly active users and 130,000 subscribers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/games/gun-disassembly/?fbs=-1&ref=br_rs|title=World of Guns: Gun Disassembly App on Facebook|accessdate=2017-01-15}}</ref>

The earlier ''Gun Disassembly'' app has "1 to 5 million installs" and 4/5 average rating listed on its [[Google Play]] Store page.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.nobleempire.GunDisassembly2&hl=en|title=Gun Disassembly 2 - Android Apps on Google Play|accessdate=2017-01-15}}</ref> It has a 4/5 rating on Apple [[App Store (iOS)|AppStore]].<ref>[https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/world-of-guns/id1143779751?mt=12 Gun Disassembly 2 on App Store]</ref>

